# Flowchart: docs-workflows-refactoring

taskId: 0963bf20-4201-494c-ad1b-32e6b476e97e

## flowchart

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    Start([Start]) --> ScanDirs[Scan docs/workflows/]
    ScanDirs --> ForEachDir{For each directory}

    ForEachDir --> CheckHalfWidth{Has half-width katakana?}
    CheckHalfWidth -->|No| CheckOldProject{Old project?}
    CheckHalfWidth -->|Yes| CheckDuplicate{Full-width pair exists?}

    CheckDuplicate -->|Yes| DiffContents{Contents identical?}
    DiffContents -->|Yes| DeleteHalf[Delete half-width dir]
    DiffContents -->|No| MergeFirst[Merge into full-width] --> DeleteHalf

    CheckDuplicate -->|No| RenameFullWidth[Rename to full-width]

    CheckOldProject -->|Yes| DeleteOld[Delete directory]
    CheckOldProject -->|No| Classify{Classify category}

    Classify --> Bugfix[bugfix/]
    Classify --> Feature[feature/]
    Classify --> WFHarness[workflow-harness/]
    Classify --> Investigation[investigation/]

    DeleteHalf --> ForEachDir
    RenameFullWidth --> Classify
    DeleteOld --> ForEachDir
    Bugfix --> MoveDir[Move to category]
    Feature --> MoveDir
    WFHarness --> MoveDir
    Investigation --> MoveDir
    MoveDir --> ForEachDir

    ForEachDir -->|Done| HandleLoose[Wrap 14 loose .md files]
    HandleLoose --> Verify[Verify AC-1 through AC-7]
    Verify --> End([End])
```

## decisions

- Half-width katakana detection uses Unicode range FF65-FF9F to identify directories needing normalization
- When a full-width counterpart exists and contents differ, merge strategy is: copy missing files from half-width into full-width, then delete half-width directory
- When a full-width counterpart exists and contents are identical, the half-width directory is deleted without merge
- When no full-width counterpart exists, the half-width directory is renamed in-place to full-width katakana
- Old project classification is based on directories belonging to completed/archived tasks that no longer have active workflow state
- Category classification uses the task prefix or content analysis: bug-related goes to bugfix/, new capability to feature/, harness changes to workflow-harness/, and exploratory work to investigation/
- Loose .md files (14 files directly under docs/workflows/) are wrapped into appropriately named subdirectories before category assignment
- Verification step checks all seven acceptance criteria (AC-1 through AC-7) as a final gate before completion
- Directory moves preserve git history by using git mv rather than filesystem mv
- The loop processes directories one at a time to avoid conflicts when half-width and full-width pairs reference the same logical project
